The paper deals with the problem of joint sparse recovery, which is a subfield of Compressed Sensing. The use of l_p-minimization subject to matrices is a common technique in this field, which suggests that the paper could belong to cs.SP (Signal Processing) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also presents theoretical results, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper includes an example to confirm the validity of the conclusions, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
